The paper discusses a method for training discriminative state estimators using gradient descent, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The method is specifically designed to handle rich sensory observations, such as camera images, which suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of "cs.CV" (Computer Vision) and "cs.RO" (Robotics). The paper also mentions the use of nonlinear function approximators such as convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique in "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
